                    In 1989, Mailer joined with a number of other prominent authors in publicly expressing support for colleague [[Salman Rushdie]], whose ''[[The Satanic Verses]]'' led to a ''[[fatwa]]'' issued by Iran's Islamic government calling for Rushdie's
                    assassination.Kaufman, Michael T. [https://www.nytimes.com/books/99/04/18/specials/rushdie-literary.html "Literary World Lashes Out After a Week of Hesitation."]
